The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, August 07, 2004 				 Rallies hold up traffic
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A string of rallies held up traffic in central and south Calcutta on Friday afternoon. 																								Handcart-pullers blocked Beadon Street and Rabindra Sarani for half-an-hour to protest police high-handedness. 																								Traffic was disrupted in central Calcutta by members of the Swarna Shilpi Bachao Committee marching to protest the marketing policy of a prominent jewellery manufacturer. The protesters marched along BB Ganguly Street, CR Avenue and JL Nehru Road. 																								Traffic on Strand Bank Road was affected when members of the Eastern Railway Mens Union held a rally at Fairlie Place to protest privatisation of facilities in the railway. 																								Also, SUCI activists held a street-corner meeting in front of Metro cinema to observe Hiroshima Day. 
